      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SERRATED EDGE (2) turned in a better effort at Ballarat last start, finishing second behind Aston Reeves (26.01) in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Top prospect. TIGER SHARK (3) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by one length at The Meadows in a handy 30.68 beating Maximum Reed. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. In sparkling form and expected to measure up again. KRAKEN CHIEF (8) was safely held last time out, finishing sixth at this track over 500m behind Doongalla Serena (28.78) in a Grade 5. Placed at his previous run. The form out of his last race has been franked. Cannot be left out. WHODAT WHISKEY (7) cannot be underestimated.",
